103 
104 template<typename S>
105 Trajectory<S>::Trajectory(const std::vector<S>& states,
106  const std::vector<double>& times)
107  : states_(states),
108  times_(times),
109  configuration_(false) {
110  // Warn if state/time lists are not the same length and truncate
111  // the longer one to match the smaller.
112  if (states_.size() != times_.size()) {
113  ROS_ERROR("Trajectory: states/times are not the same length.");
114 
115  // Resize the shorter one.
116  if (states_.size() > times_.size())
117  states_.resize(times_.size());
118  else
119  times_.resize(states_.size());
120  }
121 
122  // Make sure times are sorted. Overwrite any inversions with the larger
123  // time as we move left to right in the list.
124  for (size_t ii = 1; ii < times_.size(); ii++) {
125  if (times_[ii - 1] > times_[ii]) {
126  ROS_ERROR("Trajectory: fixing an inversion in the list of times.");
127  times_[ii] = times_[ii + 1];
128  }
129  }
130 }

132 // Construct from a ROS message.
133 template<typename S>
134 Trajectory<S>::Trajectory(const fastrack_msgs::Trajectory::ConstPtr& msg)
135  : configuration_(false) {
136  size_t num_elements = msg->states.size();
137 
138  // Get size carefully.
139  if (msg->states.size() != msg->times.size()) {
140  ROS_ERROR("Trajectory: states/times are not the same length.");
141  num_elements = std::min(msg->states.size(), msg->times.size());
142  }
143 
144  // Unpack message.
145  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < num_elements; ii++) {
146  states_.push_back(S(msg->states[ii]));
147  times_.push_back(msg->times[ii]);
148  }
149 
150  // Is this trajectory in state space or configuration space?
151  if (num_elements > 0)
152  configuration_ = msg->states.front().x.size() == S::ConfigurationDimension();
153  else
154  configuration_ = false;
155 }

157 // Interpolate at a particular time.
158 template<typename S>
159 S Trajectory<S>::Interpolate(double t) const {
160  // Get an iterator pointing to the first element in times_ that does
161  // not compare less than t.
162  const auto iter = std::lower_bound(times_.begin(), times_.end(), t);
163 
164  // Catch case where iter points to the beginning of the list.
165  // This will happen if t occurs before the first time in the list.
166  if (iter == times_.begin()) {
167  ROS_WARN_THROTTLE(1.0, "Trajectory: interpolating before first time.");
168  return states_.front();
169  }
170 
171  // Catch case where iter points to the end of the list.
172  // This will happen if t occurs after the last time in the list.
173  if (iter == times_.end()) {
174  ROS_WARN_THROTTLE(1.0, "Trajectory: interpolating after the last time.");
175  return states_.back();
176  }
177 
178  // Iterator definitely points to somewhere in the middle of the list.
179  // Get indices sandwiching t.
180  const size_t hi = (iter - times_.begin());
181  const size_t lo = hi - 1;
182 
183  // Linearly interpolate states.
184  const double frac = (t - times_[lo]) / (times_[hi] - times_[lo]);
185  S interpolated = (1.0 - frac) * states_[lo] + frac * states_[hi];
186 
187  // If this is a configuration trajectory, set non-configuration states
188  // by providing a numerical derivative of configuration.
189  if (configuration_) {
190  if (times_[hi] - times_[lo] > 1e-8)
191  interpolated.SetConfigurationDot(
192  (states_[hi] - states_[lo]).Configuration() / (times_[hi] - times_[lo]));
193  else
194  interpolated.SetConfigurationDot(
195  VectorXd::Zero(S::ConfigurationDimension()));
196  }
197 
198  return interpolated;
199 }

201 // Convert to a ROS message.
202 template <typename S>
203 fastrack_msgs::Trajectory Trajectory<S>::ToRos() const {
204  fastrack_msgs::Trajectory msg;
205 
206  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < states_.size(); ii++) {
207  msg.states.push_back(states_[ii].ToRos());
208  msg.times.push_back(times_[ii]);
209  }
210 
211  return msg;
212 }

215 // Visualize this trajectory.
216 template<typename S>
217 void Trajectory<S>::Visualize(const ros::Publisher& pub,
218  const std::string& frame) const {
219  if (pub.getNumSubscribers() == 0) {
220  ROS_WARN_THROTTLE(1.0, "Trajectory: I'm lonely. Please subscribe.");
221  return;
222  }
223 
224  // Set up spheres marker.
225  visualization_msgs::Marker spheres;
226  spheres.ns = "spheres";
227  spheres.header.frame_id = frame;
228  spheres.header.stamp = ros::Time::now();
229  spheres.id = 0;
230  spheres.type = visualization_msgs::Marker::SPHERE_LIST;
231  spheres.action = visualization_msgs::Marker::ADD;
232  spheres.scale.x = 0.1;
233  spheres.scale.y = 0.1;
234  spheres.scale.z = 0.1;
235 
236  // Set up line strip marker.
237  visualization_msgs::Marker lines;
238  lines.ns = "lines";
239  lines.header.frame_id = frame;
240  lines.header.stamp = ros::Time::now();
241  lines.id = 0;
242  lines.type = visualization_msgs::Marker::LINE_STRIP;
243  lines.action = visualization_msgs::Marker::ADD;
244  lines.scale.x = 0.05;
245 
246  // Populate markers.
247  for (size_t ii = 0; ii < states_.size(); ii++) {
248  geometry_msgs::Point p;
249  p.x = states_[ii].X();
250  p.y = states_[ii].Y();
251  p.z = states_[ii].Z();
252 
253  const std_msgs::ColorRGBA c = Colormap(times_[ii]);
254 
255  spheres.points.push_back(p);
256  spheres.colors.push_back(c);
257  lines.points.push_back(p);
258  lines.colors.push_back(c);
259  }
260 
261  // Publish.
262  pub.publish(spheres);
263  if (states_.size() > 1)
264  pub.publish(lines);
265 }

267 // Custom colormap for the given time.
268 template<typename S>
269 std_msgs::ColorRGBA Trajectory<S>::Colormap(double t) const {
270  std_msgs::ColorRGBA c;
271 
272  c.r = (Size() == 0 || Duration() < 1e-8) ? 0.0 :
273  std::max(0.0, std::min(1.0, (t - times_.front()) / Duration()));
274  c.g = 0.0;
275  c.b = 1.0 - c.r;
276  c.a = 0.9;
277 
278  return c;
279 }
